    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/30658: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11">August 11,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2516. Acting Chief Political Division Foreign Office states that reports from
                    Rome have convinced Foreign Office that Badoglio tried to make an arrangement
                    with Germany for removal of German troops from Italian soil. If successful, he
                    had intended to capitulate, but as he was unable to persuade Germans to agree to
                    this his next step is indefinite.</p>
                <p>Same officer states as his personal belief that holding tactics still in practice
                    on eastern front indicate continuation of modified “Hitler strategy” hence he
                    believes Hitler still controls military forces and that this will shorten war by
                    causing a quicker depletion of German military power than if generals had their
                    way and shortened front immediately without sure loss of men and material as
                    present strategy demands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
